<seg id=1> Lien Hoe Estimated to Redeem Remaining 65% of Bond by Year's End </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (Kuala Lumpur) Lien Hoe is estimated to redeem the remaining 65% of its 53,810,000 Ringgit bond through bank loans by the end of the year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The total issued value of the redeemable guarantee bond, at an annual interest rate of 6%, to Lien Hoe is 85,740,000 Ringgits, and the expiration date is August 17, 1998. </seg>
<seg id=4> Due to the decline in the real estate market and idle money contracted, Lien Hoe can redeem 35% of the bond at the expiration date, and the remaining 65% of the bond will be extended to the expiration date of August 17, 2000 with an annual interest rate of 15%. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> The Securities Exchange Supervisory Committee allowed Lien Hoe to extend the bond's expiration date to August 17, 2000 last month. The group is the first company to be allowed to extend its bond's expiration date. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Due to the falling market interest, Lien Hoe had planned to redeem the remainder of the bond through a bank loan, but without paying the high interest of 15% to the bond holder. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The Managing Director, Zeng Huahong, expressed that due to the falling market interest rate, and a new financial budget benefitting real estate development, Lien Hoe was predicted to turn its inferior position of this preceding year around and make good progress in the following year. </seg>
</p>
